// BOOK PAGE — ReportGenerator
//
// The ReportGenerator answers one question: given a set of sales records,
// what are the key performance statistics? It knows nothing about how those
// statistics will be displayed, where they will be stored, or how the raw
// data was acquired. This separation exists because formatting rules change
// independently of statistical logic, and persistence technology changes
// independently of both. Keeping the three concerns in separate classes
// means a change to CSV formatting never risks breaking the revenue calculation,
// and a change from file-based to cloud-based storage never touches the math.
// A caller builds a ReportGenerator, passes it raw Sale data, receives a
// ReportData value object, then hands that value object to a formatter and
// then to a writer — three small, focused objects instead of one large one.


